  "design_notes": {
    "ryu_vs_ken_philosophy": "Ryu is the balanced zoner — reliable hadouken, solid anti-air shoryuken, consistent damage. Ken is the rushdown variant — faster walk speed, higher jump arc for cross-ups, weaker fireball but stronger shoryuken damage for punishes.",
    "chun_li_philosophy": "Chun-Li is the fastest character with the best walk speed. She rewards patient charge management. Her lack of a fast overhead special is compensated by exceptional normal move speed and the hyakuretsu kyaku pressure tool.",
    "charge_management": "Charge characters must balance holding charge direction (which restricts movement) with footsies and positioning. A good Chun-Li player is always pre-charging their next special move.",
    "input_priority_rule": "Special moves always have priority over normals and system commands. This is essential for charge moves using 'up' (SBK) — the system must never process a jump when a charge special is valid."
  }
